rComments: This was the worst class I have taken so far at UCSC. The lectures were unintelligible, the prof is unclear, and almost NOBODY goes to class... the only reason I learned anything was through my TA! He was very unclear about what was going to be on the final, and I felt so understudied.. but I got a B in the class and on the final, so you have to give him credit for being fair/easy on the students, I guess.

Most unengaging teacher I have EVER had. He literally does not teach, he just writes math on the board in a slow, meticulous fashion. Soft-spoken and completely dispassionate. You are totally on your own in this class.

He goes straight from the book word for word, very unhelpful, very little leeway. Memorize your theorems or you're toast!!! His lectures are way boring and hardly anyone went to them. See your TA's for all the help you need.
